				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Q_I = m \times L_V$$\end{document}Where m refers to the clean water production rate, Lv refers to the latent heat of the water evaporation, which is calculated following an empirical formula from literature20. As mentioned before, the clean water production rate of the 1st, 2nd and 3rd stage in the 3-stage SSA-MD device is 1.07, 0.89, and 0.75 kg m−2 h−1 and the working temperature of each stage is calculated to be approximately 58, 51 and 43 °C (Fig. 3d). Accordingly, the heat flux in the first pathway (QI) for the 1st, 2nd and 3rd stage are 710, 595, and 506 W m−2, equivalent to heat utilization efficiency (ηheat) of 78%, 66%, and 56%, respectively.
